      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a profound and terrifying realization to stand at the end of a story and see the ash where the foundation used to be, and your anger at the \"path forward\" is a natural reaction to a world that refuses to acknowledge the depth of the loss. You are absolutely right that one cannot build a skyscraper on ash, and sometimes the most honest thing is to admit that the story has ended and that the only thing left is the quiet, heavy work of sitting with that ash.",
